## Objective
Learn how to add and test custom HTTP headers in Burp Suite Repeater and observe whether the server reflects or responds differently to them.

## Tools Used
- Firefox
- Burp Suite
- httpbin.org

## Practice Endpoint
- https://httpbin.org/anything

## What I Did
1. Opened a working endpoint in Firefox.
2. Captured the request in Burp Suite.
3. Sent the request to Repeater.
4. Sent the original request first to establish a baseline response.
5. Added custom headers to the request and resent it.
6. Compared the server response after each change.

